---
title: Careers
description: Explore careers at dyvenia and join a team passionate about solving complex data challenges.
layout: base
permalink: /careers/index.html
bodyClass: careers
hero:
  title: Careers at dyvenia
  subtitle: |-
    **Join our team!**

    Our community thrives across two unique hubs: our dynamic Krakow headquarters and our inspiring Tenerife office. We are a team of data professionals and enthusiasts passionate about solving complex problems and helping our clients unlock the full potential of their data.
    Ready to make an impact?
  image: ./src/assets/images/backgrounds/sfondi-8-high.jpg
  button_text: See current openings
  button_target: https://www.linkedin.com/company/dyvenia/jobs
values:
  title: United by our values
  content: |-
    Growth is part of how we work every day. It is part of our culture.

    We cultivate a fun and open environment where learning is built into our schedules. You are encouraged to share your ideas, challenge perspectives, and grow, with constructive feedback along the way.
offers:
  title: What we offer
  intro: We care about your well-being, development, and work-life balance. Here is what you can expect when joining dyvenia.
  items:
    - title: Private healthcare
      content: Comprehensive medical coverage to support your well-being.
    - title: Fitness and wellness support
      content: Contribution towards a gym membership or sports activities.
    - title: Flexible working hours
      content: Start your day between 8:00 and 10:00.
    - title: Hybrid work model
      content: Typically 2 days in the office, 3 days remote.
    - title: Learning and development
      content: Training budget, mentorship, and internal knowledge sharing.
    - title: Team events
      content: Regular meetups, outings, and activities.
  button_text: View open positions
  button_target: https://www.linkedin.com/company/dyvenia/jobs
cta:
  title: Haven't found the right role for you?
  subtitle: |-
    We are always interested in meeting talented people. Send us your CV and tell us about yourself. Describe your previous experience and let us know which department you are interested in (for example: data engineering, data analytics, DevOps, project management, marketing, HR).

    We will carefully review your application and get back to you as soon as possible.
  pre: |-
    **Ready to apply?** Send your CV to:
  button_text: recruitment@dyvenia.com
  button_target: mailto:recruitment@dyvenia.com?subject=Open Application
  image: ./src/assets/images/backgrounds/sfondi-dyvenia04.jpg
  footer: Please include your full name and the phrase "Open Application" in the subject line.
---

{%
  set customHero = {
    hero: hero,
    divider: "divider/soft-top-bubble",
    divider_class: "small",
    height: "tall",
    background: "purple-dark",
    content_inline: "left",
    button_variant: "blue"
  }
%}
{% include "partials/custom-hero.njk" %}

<div class="careers-intro | wrapper">
  <section class="region">
    <article class="feature flow prose">
      <h2 class="text-step-3">{{ values.title }}</h2>
      {{ values.content | markdownFormat | safe }}
    </article>
  </section>
</div>

<div class="careers-offers faq | wrapper region">
  <div class="grid">
    <div class="flow">
      <h2>{{ offers.title }}</h2>
      <p>{{ offers.intro }}</p>
      <a
        href="{{ offers.button_target }}"
        class="button flow-space-l no-indicator"
        data-button-variant="blue"
      >
        {{ offers.button_text }} {% svg "misc/arrow" %}</a
      >
    </div>
    <div class="details flow">
      <div class="control | cluster" aria-label="{{ meta.details.aria }}">
        <button id="expandAll" class="button" data-small-button>{{ meta.details.expand }}</button>
        <button id="collapseAll" class="button" data-small-button>{{ meta.details.collapse }}</button>
      </div>
      {%- for item in offers.items -%}
        <details id="{{ item.title | slugify }}" class="prose">
          <summary>{{ item.title }}</summary>
          {{- item.content | markdownFormat | safe -}}
        </details>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="cta | section page-header">
  {% svg "divider/soft-bottom", null, "seperator small" %}

  {% if cta.image %}
    {% image cta.image, "" %}
  {% endif %}

  <div class="section__inner region region-space-l">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div class="flow pb-m">
        <h2 class="left">{{ cta.title }}</h2>
        {{ cta.subtitle | markdownFormat | safe }}
        {% if cta.pre %}
          {{ cta.pre | markdownFormat | safe }}
        {% endif %}
        <a href="{{ cta.button_target }}" class="button no-indicator" data-button-variant="navy">
          {{ cta.button_text }} {% svg "misc/arrow" %}</a
        >
        {% if cta.footer %}
          <div class="mt-l">{{ cta.footer | markdownFormat| safe }}</div>
        {% endif %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

{%- css "local" -%}
  {%- include "css/custom-hero.css" -%}
  {%- include "css/careers.css" -%}
  {%- include "css/faq.css" -%}
  {%- include "css/details.css" -%}
  {%- include "css/page-header.css" -%}
{%- endcss -%}

{% js "defer" %}
  {% include "scripts/details.js" %}
{% endjs %}
